\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces The fundamental question in federated concept drift. \emph  {Left}: the bias-variance tradeoff---global aggregation has low variance but high interference bias; concept-level aggregation eliminates bias but raises variance (Figure~\ref {fig:tradeoff}). \emph  {Center}: the sharp crossover condition $\mathrm  {SNR} > C{-}1$ determines \emph  {whether} concept-level aggregation helps, validated on 609 synthetic configurations. \emph  {Right}: imperfect clustering acts as implicit shrinkage toward the global mean, explaining why CFL outperforms Oracle when $K/C$ is small.}}{2}{figure.1}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:tradeoff}{{1}{2}{The fundamental question in federated concept drift. \emph {Left}: the bias-variance tradeoff---global aggregation has low variance but high interference bias; concept-level aggregation eliminates bias but raises variance (Figure~\ref {fig:tradeoff}). \emph {Center}: the sharp crossover condition $\mathrm {SNR} > C{-}1$ determines \emph {whether} concept-level aggregation helps, validated on 609 synthetic configurations. \emph {Right}: imperfect clustering acts as implicit shrinkage toward the global mean, explaining why CFL outperforms Oracle when $K/C$ is small}{figure.1}{}}
